The correct answer is:
D: CREATE USER Mary WITH PASSWORD = 'strong_password';
E: GRANT ALTER ANY USER TO Mary;

Initially, only one of the administrators or the owner of the database can create users. To authorize additional users to create new users, grant that selected user the ALTER ANY USER permission, by using a statement such as: GRANT ALTER ANY USER TO Mary;

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/sql-database/sql-database-manage-logins
